OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F163A1776525067
OL,1,Wj5hw1~{4k7juhw1{$             G2/2
OL,2,W+.-'"-$/*%*%*%/"-$/*%Q,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Sun 3 May to Sun 17 May
OL,6,FSlowly evolving weather patterns are
OL,7,Flikely through the first half of May.
OL,8,FWithin this, high pressure is likely
OL,9,Fto be located somewhere to the north
OL,10,For northwest and low pressure closer
OL,11,Fto southern areas. The orientation of
OL,12,Fand proximity to the UK of each of
OL,13,Fthese features will be key to regional
OL,14,Fweather on a day-to-day basis.
OL,15,FHowever, on balance, northern and some
OL,16,Fwestern areas are likely be drier,
OL,17,Fwith southern and possibly some
OL,18,Feastern parts seeing more in the way
OL,19,Fof rain or showers. Overall,
OL,20,Ftemperatures probably close to or a
OL,21,Flittle above average, though scope for
OL,22,Fsome cold nights with late season
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Ffrost, especially in the north.
